+{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":365266,"duration_api_ms":377255,"num_turns":41,"result":"The implementation is complete. Here's a summary of what was built:\n\n**`src/index.ts`** — A constraint-based event scheduler with the following features:\n\n**Core algorithm** (informed by inversion stratagem — designed around failure avoidance rather than naive greedy placement):\n\n1. **Cycle detection**: DFS-based cycle detection in the prerequisite graph. Self-references and multi-node cycles throw errors immediately.\n\n2. **Topological ordering with constraint tightness**: Events are sorted by dependency level first, then by constraint tightness (fewest valid rooms, longest duration) within each level. This ensures the most constrained events get placed first.\n\n3. **Multi-strategy greedy search**: Tries 4 different orderings (most-constrained-first, least-constrained-first, shortest-first, longest-first) and picks the one that schedules the most events.\n\n4. **Backtracking search**: For inputs ≤ 20 events, if any events remain unscheduled after the greedy passes, a backtracking search explores different room/time combinations to maximize placements.\n\n5. **Preferred room support**: Soft constraint — preferred rooms are tried first but don't block scheduling.\n\n**Exports**: Named export `schedule`, default export `schedule`, plus all TypeScript interfaces (`Event`, `Room`, `ScheduleOptions`, `Assignment`, `ScheduleResult`).","stop_reason":null,"session_id":"e8af3046-8259-41f1-8985-41877441d905","total_cost_usd":1.3446052499999996,"usage":{"input_tokens":37,"cache_creation_input_tokens":41479,"cache_read_input_tokens":1112291,"output_tokens":19626,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":41479,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[]},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":34201,"outputTokens"